                            <comment id="13258020" author="umamaheswararao" created="Fri, 20 Apr 2012 05:06:36 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;One idea is, Balancer can populate the Region plans into Queue from LoadBalancer.&lt;br/&gt;
HMaster can initiate one thread to process the balancer plans queque. So, whenever balancer finalize one plan object, it will put into that queue. BalancerQueueProcessor(thread) can pick the plans from queue and process. But the current LoadBalancer interface does not take any queue. It will just return List of plans from balanceCluster api. Changing interface may be difficult, as the LoadBalancer is exposed one. Any alternatives without changing interface?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13883002" author="stack" created="Mon, 27 Jan 2014 17:43:53 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Resolving.  For old balancer, not for new stochastic.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
